{
  "texts": [
    "Then we feed F s to a pretrained LLM to generate ten extra tokens via a completion setup, denoted F c (typically maps to 5 ∼ 8 English words).",
    "Then R is built as the concatenation of F s and F c.",
    "We generate one harmful target R per Q and use a pair (Q, R) for adversarial suffix learning.",
    "4.2.1 Attack effectiveness.",
    "Previous optimizationbased attack methods faced limitations in high searching cost and unsatisfactory ASR."
  ]
}